The location is excellent with major attractions just a few minutes away, but if you're looking for a peaceful retreat after a day of sightseeing you won't find it here.	The communal couches, nightly happy hour and comfortable lobby are great for meeting up with everyone, relaxing, zoning out, etc.	Many open spaces with a variety of art - some good, some not so good but a wonderfull relaxing setting.	The hotel seeems to be mostly visited by couples above 30 years and it is quiet and relaxing.	We stayed in a room with a terrace which was great for relaxing with a glass of wine after a day walking around the wonderful sights of Rome.